It’s understood the chopper was flying over a farm in Rooiberg earlier on Friday when it went down, killing the only two occupants instantly. JOHANNESBURG - Two people have been killed in a helicopter crash in Limpopo. It’s understood the chopper was flying over a farm in Rooiberg earlier on Friday when it went down, killing the only two occupants instantly. Limpopo police are now investigating the cause of the crash. Spokesperson Motlafela Mojapelo said: “The police at Rooiberg opened an inquest docket after two people were killed in a helicopter crash. The two were allegedly flying from Rustenberg to Zebula Lodge when the accident happened.” (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)